# Plan: Human/LLM-readable cc-log format

## Context

Current cc-log outputs JSONL with every tool call including full file contents. The purpose is for an LLM to read the log and improve harness code. Only two things matter: **Bash commands** and **subagent information**. Everything else (Read, Edit, Grep, etc.) is noise.

## New format

Plain text, no timestamps, no JSON. File extension: `.log`.

```
== session=2d7369bd | model=claude-opus-4-6[1m] | cwd=/home/nick/project ==

> fix the bug in auth.py

Bash | cmd: npm test
  desc: Run test suite
  stdout: 3 passed, 1 failed
  stderr: (empty)

Agent | desc="Explore auth flow" | type=Explore
  prompt: Investigate the authentication flow in auth.py. Find where tokens are validated and check for expiration bugs.

[agent:a4aec043c] Bash | cmd: grep -r "token" src/auth.py
  stdout: line 42: validate_token(...)

SubagentStop | id=a4aec043c

Stop
```

## What gets logged

| Event | What to capture |
|-------|----------------|
| SessionStart | session_id (short), model, cwd |
| UserPromptSubmit | prompt text |
| PreToolUse Bash | command, description (shows intent before execution) |
| PostToolUse Bash | command, description, stdout (truncated 300 chars), stderr if non-empty |
| PostToolUseFailure Bash | command, description, stderr |
| PreToolUse Agent | description, subagent_type, **full prompt** (never truncated) |
| SubagentStart | agent_id, agent_type |
| SubagentStop | agent_id |
| Stop / SessionEnd | just the event name |

All other events (Read, Edit, Write, Grep, Glob, PreToolUse for non-Agent tools, etc.) are **silently dropped**.

## What changes

Subagent Bash calls carry `agent_id` - prefix with `[agent:<short_id>]`.

### Hooks to keep

Only install hooks for the events we actually log:
- SessionStart, SessionEnd, UserPromptSubmit, Stop
- PostToolUse, PostToolUseFailure (filtered to Bash only in the script)
- PreToolUse (filtered to Bash and Agent in the script)
- SubagentStart, SubagentStop

Drop: PreCompact, PostCompact, PermissionRequest, PermissionDenied, TaskCreated, TaskCompleted, StopFailure (9 -> 9 hooks instead of 16).

